# Day 22 of #100DaysOfCode

Today I solved the following LeetCode problem in C++:

## âœ… 412. Fizz Buzz  
**Problem Link:** [Fizz Buzz](https://leetcode.com/problems/fizz-buzz/)  
**Approach:** Iterated from 1 to n and applied conditions to check for divisibility by 3, 5, and both to generate the expected output.

```cpp
class Solution {
public:
    vector<string> fizzBuzz(int n) {
        vector<string> ans(n);
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            if (i % 3 == 0 && i % 5 == 0)
                ans[i - 1] = "FizzBuzz";
            else if (i % 3 == 0)
                ans[i - 1] = "Fizz";
            else if (i % 5 == 0)
                ans[i - 1] = "Buzz";
            else
                ans[i - 1] = to_string(i);
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

